<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-06-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-06-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="98" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d98">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/932.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador to Great
                                    Britain</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-10">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 10, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Regarding the declaration of the special rights of Japan and Russia in
                            Mongolia and Manchuria, Langley says the British Government will admit
                            such rights but will at the same time affirm the principle of the open
                            door.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Reid</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>